==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[trigamos]]'', from ''tri'' (three) + ''gamos'' (marriage)

===Noun===
'''trigamy''' (''uncountable'')
#The state of having three (legal or illegal) [[spouse|spouses]] simultaneously.
#''(ecclesiastical)'' A third marriage.

